1
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:40,130
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:43,130
[Episode 19]

3
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:43,780
I'm not going.

4
00:01:43,780 --> 00:01:45,000
My dad will beat the hell out of me.

5
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,400
If he hits you, I'll stop—

6
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,430
Everyone, get out of the car!

7
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:25,250
There are antelopes over here.

8
00:02:26,060 --> 00:02:27,790
There are antelopes over here.

9
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:54,740
What are you doing?

10
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:55,470
Hurry up.

11
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:01,500
Coming.

12
00:03:04,930 --> 00:03:06,390
The antelope is too heavy.

13
00:05:00,430 --> 00:05:01,720
Do my dad and the others

14
00:05:01,810 --> 00:05:02,600
usually enter the mountains

15
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,530
just to fight

16
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,620
with those people?

17
00:05:07,060 --> 00:05:07,860
Not just them.

18
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:11,470
There are also placer gold diggers

19
00:05:11,660 --> 00:05:13,190
and brine shrimp catchers.

20
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:15,530
We've even run into wild yaks,

21
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:16,980
wolves,

22
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:18,120
bears,

23
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,540
and snow leopards.

24
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:21,160
Animals

25
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:22,440
act on instinct.

26
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:25,320
Humans are harder to predict.

27
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:29,130
Outside the Uninhabited Zone,

28
00:05:29,130 --> 00:05:30,540
we deal with people.

29
00:05:32,670 --> 00:05:33,890
After entering this zone,

30
00:05:33,890 --> 00:05:35,600
we deal with humanity.

31
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,540
Who said that?

32
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:40,200
Captain Duojie.

33
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:44,980
Let's go back.

34
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:49,840
Let's go back.

35
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,740
This river

36
00:05:54,770 --> 00:05:55,800
is not far from here.

37
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,010
We'll go check it out,

38
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,330
then we'll head back.

39
00:05:59,180 --> 00:05:59,740
Okay.

40
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:47,680
Wait for me here.

41
00:06:50,890 --> 00:06:52,390
Have a cigarette, brother.

42
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:53,390
Have a cigarette.

43
00:06:57,010 --> 00:06:58,540
Brother, have a cigarette.

44
00:07:02,770 --> 00:07:04,300
Have a cigarette, brother.

45
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:07,630
Brother,

46
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,560
have a cigarette.

47
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:10,630
I don't smoke.

48
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:12,890
Brother.

49
00:07:13,770 --> 00:07:15,100
Is this the Wulan River?

50
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,100
Where are you from?

51
00:07:23,970 --> 00:07:24,450
I used to work

52
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:26,190
at Zhuoyuan Lake

53
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:27,180
with San.

54
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:29,700
This isn't

55
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,800
San's territory.

56
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,190
I quit recently.

57
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:36,490
I worked my ass off day and night,

58
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,530
but the boss took all the money.

59
00:07:38,570 --> 00:07:40,040
I only hid a few grains of placer gold,

60
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,570
and he wanted to kick me out.

61
00:07:41,810 --> 00:07:43,010
So, fine, I'll leave.

62
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,450
It's pointless anyway.

63
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,040
Did he let you go?

64
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:48,980
He can beat me one-on-one,

65
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:51,159
but he can't beat all of us together.

66
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:51,900
My little brother

67
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:52,890
came out with me.

68
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,130
We got separated when we escaped.

69
00:07:55,130 --> 00:07:56,860
So I have to look around for him.

70
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:00,810
How does the kid look?

71
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,300
He's about my height.

72
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:03,910
Tan skin.

73
00:08:04,030 --> 00:08:05,110
Looks very honest.

74
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:07,710
Brother, have you seen him?

75
00:08:09,190 --> 00:08:10,010
No.

76
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:11,860
Out here,

77
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,570
I've never seen an honest man.

78
00:08:13,570 --> 00:08:14,810
What are you looking at?

79
00:08:14,810 --> 00:08:16,340
What's wrong with looking?

80
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:19,600
Come look.

81
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:20,830
There's food here.

82
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:21,950
Come here.

83
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:23,130
There's food and drink.

84
00:08:23,130 --> 00:08:23,830
Hurry.

85
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,540
What are you doing?

86
00:08:25,860 --> 00:08:26,740
You can't take that.

87
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,270
Don't move.

88
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:27,890
What are you doing?

89
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:28,330
Brother.

90
00:08:28,330 --> 00:08:28,770
What are you doing?

91
00:08:28,770 --> 00:08:29,300
Brother.

92
00:08:29,330 --> 00:08:30,340
Hey, guys!

93
00:08:30,370 --> 00:08:30,920
What's wrong?

94
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:31,870
You're not being fair, kid.

95
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:32,470
What is it?

96
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,220
There's food on the truck

97
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,200
and you didn't share with us.

98
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,059
Yeah, exactly.

99
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,010
We still have to go find someone.

100
00:08:37,010 --> 00:08:37,909
We really can't share.

101
00:08:37,909 --> 00:08:38,400
That won't do.

102
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,730
You have to give us some.

103
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:40,549
Brother.

104
00:08:40,549 --> 00:08:41,330
What are you doing?

105
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:42,409
Who are you pushing, kid?

106
00:08:42,409 --> 00:08:42,909
Brother.

107
00:08:42,909 --> 00:08:43,620
Who are you pushing?

108
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:44,150
Get lost.

109
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:44,860
Don't move.

110
00:08:45,010 --> 00:08:46,150
Go!

111
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,340
Hurry, leave!

112
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,740
Don’t move.

113
00:08:49,620 --> 00:08:50,680
What are you doing?

114
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:51,860
Tashi.

115
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:52,540
Don't move.

116
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,690
Take it back.

117
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:57,410
Tashi.

118
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,580
Tashi.

119
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,430
The blood isn't dry yet.

120
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:39,890
Shots were fired.

121
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:41,220
There are bullet holes.

122
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:43,370
It just happened.

123
00:09:43,370 --> 00:09:44,900
Not more than half a day ago.

124
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,980
This is Tashi's knife.

125
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:56,170
Get in.

126
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:57,480
Chase them.

127
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:58,040
Let's go.

128
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,250
Stop right there.

129
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:13,220
Stop right there.

130
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:15,500
Don't move.

131
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:19,750
Don't beat me.

132
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:20,550
Don't beat me.

133
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,000
Still trying to run away?

134
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:23,170
Get up.

135
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:24,630
Get up.

136
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:27,240
Behave.

137
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:27,550
Move.

138
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:27,840
Behave.

139
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,100
I...

140
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:29,740
I won't move. I won't move.

141
00:10:29,740 --> 00:10:30,470
I won't move.

142
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:32,300
Hurry. Get up there.

143
00:10:32,610 --> 00:10:33,340
Get up there.

144
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:38,840
You all better behave.

145
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:40,620
Lie down.

146
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:41,790
Behave yourselves.

147
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:43,910
Don’t move.

148
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:44,910
The Mountain Patrol is here!

149
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:45,630
The Mountain Patrol is here!

150
00:10:45,630 --> 00:10:46,980
The Mountain Patrol is here!

151
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:47,720
Dad is here.

152
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:48,840
Dad is here.

153
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:54,910
Don't shoot at the truck.

154
00:10:55,820 --> 00:10:56,410
Get in.

155
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:57,620
Get in, quick.

156
00:10:59,120 --> 00:10:59,940
Mountain Patrol!

157
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:01,400
Help us, Mountain Patrol!

158
00:11:01,530 --> 00:11:02,360
We're over here!

159
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,150
Dad!

160
00:11:03,740 --> 00:11:04,170
Dad!

161
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:29,290
Don't move.

162
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:43,910
The lung's punctured.

163
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,250
Who sent you?

164
00:11:45,870 --> 00:11:46,930
H-help me.

165
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,340
Help me.

166
00:11:49,460 --> 00:11:51,060
Why are you catching people?

167
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:53,510
Wake up!

168
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:54,620
Stay with me!

169
00:11:58,870 --> 00:11:59,800
Wait, wait.

170
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:03,480
Easy.

171
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:05,650
Dad!

172
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,000
Bastard!

173
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:08,650
Your mother is so worried!

174
00:12:08,650 --> 00:12:09,500
Dad...

175
00:12:18,690 --> 00:12:19,880
Dad...

176
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,220
Ju.

177
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,400
Did I teach you driving for this?

178
00:12:59,150 --> 00:12:59,840
Causing trouble!

179
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:00,410
I won't do it again, Ju.

180
00:13:00,410 --> 00:13:01,230
You liar!

181
00:13:01,290 --> 00:13:02,220
How dare you lie!

182
00:13:02,530 --> 00:13:03,150
Causing a mess!

183
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,080
Alright, alright.

184
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:04,940
That's enough.

185
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:05,500
Touch the car again,

186
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,510
and I'll break your arms.

187
00:13:06,510 --> 00:13:07,310
Do you hear me?

188
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,770
He's miserable enough.
Why did you hit him?

189
00:13:16,490 --> 00:13:17,550
I have to beat him up

190
00:13:18,370 --> 00:13:19,460
so he can stay.

191
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,170
Makes sense.

192
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,420
Why did they catch you all?

193
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,570
I don't know.

194
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:42,790
We went to the river

195
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:43,530
to ask them

196
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,600
about my brother.

197
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,590
Suddenly, two cars came.

198
00:13:46,590 --> 00:13:47,240
Without a word,

199
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,370
they started beating and grabbing us.

200
00:13:49,820 --> 00:13:51,550
They dragged us onto the truck.

201
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:53,600
Do you have a grudge

202
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:54,860
against those people?

203
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:57,000
We don't know them.

204
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:01,390
What about you?

205
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,480
We...

206
00:14:03,580 --> 00:14:04,080
We don't know them.

207
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:04,570
Don't know them.

208
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:05,500
I don't either.

209
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:10,840
I... I might have seen them before.

210
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:14,260
When they took me and my brother,

211
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,000
it was exactly like this.

212
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:17,370
Was it the same group?

213
00:14:19,010 --> 00:14:19,750
Not sure.

214
00:14:20,370 --> 00:14:21,500
But it seems like it.

215
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:23,370
It was also a Jeep

216
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:24,330
and a truck.

217
00:14:26,170 --> 00:14:27,700
The accent was similar too.

218
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:32,700
Captain.

219
00:14:33,370 --> 00:14:34,830
There are pelts in the car.

220
00:14:54,170 --> 00:14:54,670
Look.

221
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,370
These are all pelts.

222
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,690
Same question.

223
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,840
Why would poachers catch so many people?

224
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,120
It doesn't make sense.

225
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:04,150
Anything else?

226
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,530
There's a lot more here.

227
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:08,250
And this.

228
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:10,750
Never seen this before.

229
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:12,730
Ammonium nitrate.

230
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:14,770
It's fertilizer.

231
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:16,700
What do they need fertilizer for?

232
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,390
Yeah.

233
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:19,870
Bolamula has nothing but meadows,

234
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:21,360
swamps, and permafrost.

235
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:23,370
You can't grow crops here.

236
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:27,310
Explosives.

237
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:29,200
Explosives.

238
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:34,360
If you plane this much wood into sawdust,

239
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,430
mix it with fertilizer,

240
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:38,270
and add diesel,

241
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,140
you can make

242
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:41,700
very powerful explosives.

243
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:44,310
Why are they making explosives?

244
00:15:45,330 --> 00:15:47,390
To blow up our warehouse, obviously.

245
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,030
Could it be

246
00:16:04,980 --> 00:16:06,710
they're going to mine for gold?

247
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:08,290
That makes sense.

248
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:10,220
Gold mines need

249
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:11,250
a lot of laboru.

250
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:14,500
Recruiting outsiders is too risky.

251
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:15,910
These fossickers

252
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:17,040
came in on their own.

253
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:20,040
They're experienced and hardworking.

254
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,170
Even if they go missing,

255
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:23,670
no one will investigate.

256
00:16:24,010 --> 00:16:25,540
This is going to be trouble.

257
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,630
If inside the Uninhabited Zone,

258
00:16:27,630 --> 00:16:29,630
there really is a large-scale gold mine,

259
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:31,960
we must report to the county immediately.

260
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,480
We're just guessing right now.

261
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,140
We don't have solid evidence.

262
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:37,170
Those people don't know anything.

263
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:39,500
They can't even be considered witnesses.

264
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:40,890
We still have gas.

265
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:42,360
Should we keep chasing?

266
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:56,990
Li,

267
00:16:57,060 --> 00:16:58,340
would you like a lunch box?

268
00:16:58,340 --> 00:16:58,960
No thanks.

269
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:08,849
Zhang,

270
00:17:08,849 --> 00:17:09,780
have a lunch box.

271
00:17:12,310 --> 00:17:12,770
Dr. Wei,

272
00:17:12,849 --> 00:17:13,660
try my new dish.

273
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:14,400
It's Sichuan style.

274
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,000
No thanks.

275
00:17:25,510 --> 00:17:26,030
Party Secretary.

276
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:26,700
Director Zhang.

277
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:27,369
What's up?

278
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,830
Have you eaten?

279
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:30,650
I just finished a surgery.

280
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:31,850
I was just about to go.

281
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,240
Come on, let's go.

282
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:34,570
Let's go to the cafeteria together.

283
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:35,590
Wait a moment.

284
00:17:38,610 --> 00:17:39,670
There's something

285
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:41,390
I want to discuss with you.

286
00:17:42,430 --> 00:17:43,160
Please, sit.

287
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:51,760
It's like this.

288
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:52,980
You know, a while back,

289
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:55,290
that fund for the shower room renovation,

290
00:17:55,290 --> 00:17:55,800
didn't we

291
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,260
use it for something else?

292
00:17:57,570 --> 00:17:58,630
Some comrades

293
00:17:58,840 --> 00:17:59,860
have issues with it

294
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:01,120
and have been upset.

295
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,720
Someone even

296
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:04,190
reported this

297
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:06,150
to the Municipal Health Bureau.

298
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:07,830
They say you

299
00:18:07,940 --> 00:18:09,140
abused your position

300
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,570
for personal gain

301
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,880
and profited from it.

302
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:15,940
Also, they say you

303
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:18,050
arranged for your family members

304
00:18:18,050 --> 00:18:19,100
to run businesses

305
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:21,070
in the hospital

306
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:37,000
Bai Ji.

307
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:38,900
Bai Ji.

308
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:42,760
You haven't eaten yet, right?

309
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,600
I made this especially for you.

310
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,180
Here.

311
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:50,830
For today,

312
00:18:51,570 --> 00:18:52,490
can you stop selling food

313
00:18:52,490 --> 00:18:53,230
here?

314
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,310
Why?

315
00:18:57,420 --> 00:18:58,240
I know.

316
00:18:58,330 --> 00:18:59,370
This is purely

317
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,240
false accusations to settle scores.

318
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,960
Bai Ji has
the necessary licenses and permits.

319
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:03,890
To reduce the pressure on logistics,

320
00:19:03,890 --> 00:19:05,520
our hospital

321
00:19:05,710 --> 00:19:08,030
allows limited food-service operations.

322
00:19:08,030 --> 00:19:09,830
It is compliant and reasonable.

323
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:12,980
However,

324
00:19:14,970 --> 00:19:16,030
Bai Ji has a record.

325
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:17,660
Some people

326
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:19,450
just won't let it go.

327
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,740
If this fuss continues,

328
00:19:22,380 --> 00:19:23,360
for you

329
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:24,420
and the hospital,

330
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:26,610
it won't look good.

331
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:29,480
So,

332
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:30,500
Director Zhang.

333
00:19:30,790 --> 00:19:31,440
Can you

334
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,500
ask Bai Ji

335
00:19:33,530 --> 00:19:35,990
to stop selling lunch boxes
in the hospital?

336
00:19:38,610 --> 00:19:39,180
No.

337
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:45,220
Bai Ji did make a mistake.

338
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:47,640
But he has already

339
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:49,100
accepted his punishment.

340
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:51,480
This time,

341
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:53,210
he hasn't done anything wrong.

342
00:19:55,170 --> 00:19:57,160
There are few restaurants

343
00:19:57,570 --> 00:19:59,370
in our county town to begin with.

344
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,380
It has always been a problem

345
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:01,930
for the hospital staff and patients

346
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:03,350
to get meals.

347
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:06,550
Bai Ji selling lunch boxes here

348
00:20:06,890 --> 00:20:08,620
solves a problem for everyone,

349
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,830
and he is very popular.

350
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:13,370
The food he makes is

351
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:15,110
affordable

352
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:18,160
and clean.

353
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,460
He puts his heart into it.

354
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:26,200
As

355
00:20:27,010 --> 00:20:28,180
a mother,

356
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:32,610
I'm very proud.

357
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:39,640
My child

358
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,440
did nothing wrong

359
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:42,630
this time.

360
00:20:44,820 --> 00:20:45,630
So I do not agree.

361
00:20:45,630 --> 00:20:46,430
Don't go in.

362
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:49,220
This has nothing to do with my mom.

363
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:50,020
Tell me,

364
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:51,890
who went to the Bureau to make a scene?

365
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:52,960
Bai Ji, you go out first.

366
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,290
Party Secretary, tell me,

367
00:20:54,290 --> 00:20:55,840
-who is it?
-Bai Ji, get out!

368
00:20:56,530 --> 00:20:58,390
It's not your place to speak here.

369
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,090
Get out!

370
00:21:00,070 --> 00:21:00,600
Let's go.

371
00:21:11,470 --> 00:21:12,500
Shouting like this

372
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:13,910
solves nothing.

373
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:16,200
You're just causing trouble for ma'am.

374
00:21:16,290 --> 00:21:17,050
You have to trust her.

375
00:21:17,050 --> 00:21:18,910
She can definitely resolve this.

376
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:28,810
Stop making a scene.

377
00:21:33,050 --> 00:21:34,050
Party Secretary.

378
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:35,460
All these years,

379
00:21:36,510 --> 00:21:37,360
the one I've neglected the most

380
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:38,830
is my youngest son.

381
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:42,790
I don't blame anyone for making a fuss.

382
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:45,300
As the Director,

383
00:21:46,570 --> 00:21:48,030
I haven't done my job well.

384
00:21:52,830 --> 00:21:54,050
But this time,

385
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:56,330
I can't force Bai Ji to leave.

386
00:21:57,510 --> 00:21:59,390
If there is any negative impact,

387
00:22:00,730 --> 00:22:01,990
just punish me.

388
00:22:21,910 --> 00:22:22,680
You're back.

389
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,130
How was business today?

390
00:22:28,540 --> 00:22:29,200
It was okay.

391
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:34,220
There's so much left over.

392
00:22:37,780 --> 00:22:39,280
That's not how you do it.

393
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:41,480
You have to soak these in hot water,

394
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,940
or the grease won't come off.

395
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:43,350
Here,

396
00:22:51,150 --> 00:22:51,870
let me do it.

397
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,140
Take a break.

398
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:54,320
Brother,

399
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:55,500
have you eaten?

400
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,430
Not yet.

401
00:22:57,370 --> 00:22:57,960
Great.

402
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:00,010
Help me finish one.

403
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:02,630
Here.

404
00:23:04,990 --> 00:23:06,700
If this food sits overnight,

405
00:23:08,730 --> 00:23:09,730
it'll go to waste.

406
00:23:19,410 --> 00:23:20,000
How is it?

407
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:24,260
Your boiled pork slices

408
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:25,650
are pretty good.

409
00:23:25,710 --> 00:23:27,640
You've been practicing secretly.

410
00:23:28,290 --> 00:23:29,290
Just a little bit.

411
00:23:30,330 --> 00:23:30,860
Brother,

412
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:32,510
do you think there's anything

413
00:23:32,510 --> 00:23:33,910
that needs improvement?

414
00:23:37,390 --> 00:23:38,080
I think the flavor

415
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:38,970
is a bit bland.

416
00:23:39,290 --> 00:23:39,580
But

417
00:23:39,610 --> 00:23:40,770
considering it's for patients,

418
00:23:40,770 --> 00:23:42,570
too much seasoning wouldn't be good.

419
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:44,570
I think it's just right. It's tasty.

420
00:23:48,430 --> 00:23:49,000
Okay.

421
00:23:49,580 --> 00:23:50,750
If you say it's good,

422
00:23:52,860 --> 00:23:53,230
then

423
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:54,700
I...

424
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:55,940
I have no regrets.

425
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,880
Since the food is so good,

426
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:12,840
why didn't any of it sell?

427
00:24:16,490 --> 00:24:17,550
It doesn't matter.

428
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:19,980
Whether it sells

429
00:24:20,570 --> 00:24:21,900
or how much money I make,

430
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,740
I don't actually care.

431
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:26,680
I just dream of

432
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:29,490
making these lunch boxes amazing.

433
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:37,020
I picked every single vegetable leaf

434
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:39,240
with care.

435
00:24:40,810 --> 00:24:42,340
I learned how to pair dishes

436
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:43,950
and how to plate them.

437
00:24:45,510 --> 00:24:47,770
I even learned dietary therapy from Yan.

438
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:49,950
Which dishes suit which illness,

439
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,810
and how much oil and salt to use

440
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:55,930
for these patient meals.

441
00:24:57,560 --> 00:24:58,440
I chased after her

442
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,780
every day asking about it.

443
00:25:07,430 --> 00:25:07,960
Brother.

444
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:12,460
You and the sisters

445
00:25:14,300 --> 00:25:16,610
are all so successful.

446
00:25:17,930 --> 00:25:19,930
But what about me?

447
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:22,940
I-I feel like

448
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:26,340
I was just starting to make something
of myself.

449
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:31,200
I could finally hold my head up

450
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:32,420
in front of Yan.

451
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,240
Not causing trouble for the family

452
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,400
or Mom.

453
00:25:40,140 --> 00:25:40,640
But

454
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:42,350
why did...

455
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:45,970
What is wrong with you?

456
00:25:47,590 --> 00:25:49,130
Isn't Mom happy too?

457
00:25:50,570 --> 00:25:51,550
What happened?

458
00:25:53,110 --> 00:25:54,460
Isn't everything fine?

459
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:55,280
It's nothing.

460
00:25:55,750 --> 00:25:56,810
It doesn't matter.

461
00:25:57,090 --> 00:25:58,150
It doesn't matter.

462
00:25:58,500 --> 00:25:59,530
As long as you

463
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:00,850
enjoy the food

464
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:02,270
and Mom is happy,

465
00:26:02,810 --> 00:26:03,670
that's enough.

466
00:26:05,010 --> 00:26:06,140
I've made up my mind.

467
00:26:07,870 --> 00:26:08,770
I won't go to the hospital

468
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:10,370
to sell lunch boxes anymore.

469
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,480
Why not?

470
00:26:13,930 --> 00:26:14,390
Mom.

471
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:16,180
Mom.

472
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:19,310
I'm sorry.

473
00:26:20,290 --> 00:26:22,290
I... I caused trouble for you again.

474
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:25,660
I've decided.

475
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,760
I won't go back

476
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:30,310
to the hospital.

477
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:33,890
What about your future?

478
00:26:34,690 --> 00:26:36,090
What will you do then?

479
00:26:42,660 --> 00:26:43,520
Remember this.

480
00:26:45,070 --> 00:26:47,400
In the future,
whenever you make a decision,

481
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:49,260
you must really think it through.

482
00:26:50,050 --> 00:26:51,710
Don't always be so impulsive.

483
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:57,500
Bai Ji.

484
00:26:58,450 --> 00:26:59,050
Come here.

485
00:27:05,980 --> 00:27:06,910
Wipe your tears.

486
00:27:07,290 --> 00:27:08,220
Wipe your tears.

487
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:26,420
Sit down.

488
00:27:35,270 --> 00:27:36,200
Your share,

489
00:27:37,110 --> 00:27:38,770
I'll give it to you in advance.

490
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:39,720
Mom.

491
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:41,350
Are you...

492
00:27:41,350 --> 00:27:42,830
kicking me out?

493
00:27:43,790 --> 00:27:45,070
What are you thinking?

494
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:46,700
Then...

495
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:48,180
why are you giving me this?

496
00:27:51,120 --> 00:27:52,250
Over the years,

497
00:27:52,940 --> 00:27:54,510
I've saved 6,000 yuan.

498
00:27:55,130 --> 00:27:56,130
Each of you siblings

499
00:27:56,130 --> 00:27:57,110
get a share.

500
00:27:58,250 --> 00:27:59,760
When your eldest sister went to Guangzhou,

501
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,270
I gave her 1,500.

502
00:28:01,850 --> 00:28:02,640
Now,

503
00:28:03,870 --> 00:28:05,270
I'm giving you 1,500 too.

504
00:28:08,010 --> 00:28:09,770
I don't know now,

505
00:28:10,260 --> 00:28:12,040
how much the rent for a shop is.

506
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:13,950
You might have to

507
00:28:13,950 --> 00:28:15,210
chip in a bit yourself.

508
00:28:17,380 --> 00:28:18,750
Go open a shop.

509
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,350
Open a shop?

510
00:28:23,150 --> 00:28:24,810
Your cooking is so delicious.

511
00:28:26,170 --> 00:28:27,220
I support you.

512
00:28:41,570 --> 00:28:43,400
My son has a skill now.

513
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:47,740
Remember what your grandpa said?

514
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:50,200
A man with a skill

515
00:28:50,670 --> 00:28:52,130
will never go hungry.

516
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,140
No.

517
00:28:54,510 --> 00:28:55,640
I can't take it, Mom.

518
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:56,470
I'm too ashamed.

519
00:28:56,470 --> 00:28:57,480
Didn't I say?

520
00:28:57,510 --> 00:28:58,900
One share each.

521
00:29:00,110 --> 00:29:00,740
This money

522
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:02,420
will be yours sooner or later.

523
00:29:05,030 --> 00:29:05,890
I...

524
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:07,990
I'm afraid I won't succeed.

525
00:29:10,470 --> 00:29:11,080
Bai Ji.

526
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:14,280
Where there's a will, there's a way.

527
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,730
Growing up,

528
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,970
how much trouble did you cause?

529
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:20,450
How many times did you stumble?

530
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,010
But every time

531
00:29:23,010 --> 00:29:24,270
you were knocked down,

532
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:25,860
you stood back up.

533
00:29:28,050 --> 00:29:29,090
I believe in you.

534
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:37,250
Mom.

535
00:29:48,930 --> 00:29:50,870
I clearly love you.

536
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:54,540
And you thought I was kicking you out.

537
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,100
It seems all these years,

538
00:30:00,530 --> 00:30:01,930
I haven't done a good job.

539
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:03,260
No, no, no.

540
00:30:03,990 --> 00:30:04,950
Don't blame me.

541
00:30:05,920 --> 00:30:07,070
I don't. I don't.

542
00:30:15,020 --> 00:30:16,200
You're a grown man now,

543
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:16,920
are still hiding in my arms

544
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:17,720
crying?

545
00:30:17,810 --> 00:30:18,940
Aren't you ashamed?

546
00:30:21,670 --> 00:30:22,620
No, I'm not.

547
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:27,140
Here.

548
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:28,800
My veteran's allowance.

549
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:29,860
To give you a boost.

550
00:30:31,590 --> 00:30:32,000
I...

551
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:33,850
How can I take this, Brother?

552
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:36,030
I now have food

553
00:30:36,050 --> 00:30:36,940
and shelter at home.

554
00:30:36,940 --> 00:30:37,800
I don't need it.

555
00:30:38,140 --> 00:30:38,770
No way.

556
00:30:38,940 --> 00:30:39,980
You'll need it later.

557
00:30:39,980 --> 00:30:41,140
You have to get married.

558
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,460
There are many things
you have to spend on.

559
00:30:42,460 --> 00:30:42,770
I...

560
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:44,070
Come on. Just take it.

561
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,980
Your cooking is so good.

562
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:47,780
Open a restaurant and work hard.

563
00:30:47,810 --> 00:30:48,870
I'm waiting for you

564
00:30:48,870 --> 00:30:50,270
to build Mom a nice house.

565
00:30:51,130 --> 00:30:52,460
I'll look forward to it.

566
00:31:04,970 --> 00:31:06,500
I'll definitely work hard.

567
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:17,870
[Mazhi County Public Security Bureau]

568
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:32,090
Thanks.

569
00:31:36,090 --> 00:31:36,770
Does the Mountain Patrol

570
00:31:36,770 --> 00:31:37,900
not go into the mountains anymore

571
00:31:37,900 --> 00:31:39,760
and are investigating cases now?

572
00:31:39,980 --> 00:31:41,680
Checking the poachers' backgrounds

573
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:42,980
helps us work better.

574
00:31:46,710 --> 00:31:47,480
Are you eating here

575
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,410
for lunch today?

576
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:50,750
Yeah.

577
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:53,350
I need to borrow some meal tickets
from you.

578
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:56,140
Then you should pay up.

579
00:31:56,750 --> 00:31:57,820
Okay.

580
00:32:04,330 --> 00:32:05,590
We stock dozens of tons

581
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:07,350
of this fertilizer every year.

582
00:32:07,770 --> 00:32:08,240
Look,

583
00:32:08,310 --> 00:32:10,110
we stocked forty tons this year.

584
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:10,710
Here.

585
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:14,210
Can you tell me

586
00:32:14,210 --> 00:32:15,240
who bought it?

587
00:32:16,030 --> 00:32:17,230
Just the bulk buyers.

588
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:18,820
That's impossible to say.

589
00:32:19,190 --> 00:32:21,010
Farmers and herdsmen from nearby townships

590
00:32:21,010 --> 00:32:22,030
all buy from us.

591
00:32:22,810 --> 00:32:24,340
Some buy three or five bags.

592
00:32:24,710 --> 00:32:25,930
Some buy a dozen bags

593
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,410
to share among a few people.

594
00:32:27,410 --> 00:32:28,810
So what counts as bulk?

595
00:32:29,830 --> 00:32:30,830
Besides,

596
00:32:30,940 --> 00:32:33,460
buying fertilizer
doesn't require registration.

597
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:34,720
How can I check for you?

598
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,010
I can only tell you

599
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:37,570
who bought some in the last few days.

600
00:32:37,570 --> 00:32:38,470
Before that,

601
00:32:38,610 --> 00:32:40,010
I really can't remember.

602
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:44,740
Why don't

603
00:32:44,980 --> 00:32:45,650
you go ask

604
00:32:45,810 --> 00:32:47,090
the other counties?

605
00:32:47,610 --> 00:32:48,570
We asked.

606
00:32:48,620 --> 00:32:50,640
They said pretty much the same thing.

607
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:52,180
Then I can't help you.

608
00:32:53,170 --> 00:32:53,980
Alright. Sorry to bother you.

609
00:32:53,980 --> 00:32:54,640
No worries.

610
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:08,220
Shao Yunfei sent this.

611
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:10,700
-How thoughtful of Reporter Shao.
-Ju.

612
00:33:10,700 --> 00:33:12,030
Let me get you some rice.

613
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:12,670
Let's see

614
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,020
what's inside.

615
00:33:14,540 --> 00:33:15,480
Is there any alcohol?

616
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:16,270
I don't know.

617
00:33:16,620 --> 00:33:17,680
Look for yourself.

618
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:19,990
He.

619
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:21,420
Take some of it

620
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:23,050
together with the recent supplies,

621
00:33:23,050 --> 00:33:24,070
and send them to the brothers

622
00:33:24,070 --> 00:33:24,790
at the station tomorrow.

623
00:33:24,790 --> 00:33:25,140
Okay.

624
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,700
Keep the ham sausages.

625
00:33:26,850 --> 00:33:28,110
Keep the ham sausages.

626
00:33:29,210 --> 00:33:30,130
There's no alcohol.

627
00:33:30,130 --> 00:33:32,060
But there are liqueur chocolates.

628
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:35,290
Does this count as alcohol?

629
00:33:35,290 --> 00:33:36,180
It does.

630
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,390
Liquor chocolates.

631
00:33:40,210 --> 00:33:40,820
Captain.

632
00:33:41,430 --> 00:33:42,560
Is chocolate candy.

633
00:33:46,690 --> 00:33:48,010
not liquor chocolate?

634
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:49,380
Why is there no alcohol in it?

635
00:33:49,380 --> 00:33:50,010
I drank it.

636
00:33:54,700 --> 00:33:55,160
What are you laughing at?

637
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:56,560
Just to make you jealous.

638
00:33:57,510 --> 00:33:58,550
It's not good.

639
00:33:59,540 --> 00:34:00,480
It really isn't.

640
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:10,530
How's the file check going?

641
00:34:11,139 --> 00:34:12,670
That truck has fake plates.

642
00:34:13,370 --> 00:34:14,830
The VIN code was filed off,

643
00:34:14,940 --> 00:34:16,600
so we couldn't find the owner.

644
00:34:17,540 --> 00:34:18,940
As for the illegal gold mining files,

645
00:34:18,940 --> 00:34:20,670
we haven't found any leads yet.

646
00:34:23,239 --> 00:34:24,440
How about on your end?

647
00:34:27,010 --> 00:34:27,920
No progress

648
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,480
at the Supply and Marketing Cooperative
either.

649
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,080
We went to several counties.

650
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:32,030
Buying fertilizer

651
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:33,830
doesn't require registration.

652
00:34:34,900 --> 00:34:35,900
Just as I thought.

653
00:34:36,710 --> 00:34:37,920
Based on our theory,

654
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:39,889
if inside the Uninhabited Zone,

655
00:34:39,889 --> 00:34:40,380
there really is

656
00:34:40,380 --> 00:34:41,900
blasting and mining,

657
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:43,650
the mine could operate

658
00:34:43,830 --> 00:34:45,000
in two ways.

659
00:34:45,780 --> 00:34:46,940
One is to transport the ore out

660
00:34:46,940 --> 00:34:47,900
for processing.

661
00:34:48,469 --> 00:34:49,719
Two is to smelt the ore

662
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:51,420
in the zone

663
00:34:51,940 --> 00:34:53,469
and transport the gold out.

664
00:34:55,820 --> 00:34:57,110
Transporting ore out

665
00:34:58,010 --> 00:34:59,470
would be too conspicuous.

666
00:34:59,750 --> 00:35:01,010
That's not realistic.

667
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:03,930
Unless they have heavy trucks.

668
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:08,710
That's a line of investigation.

669
00:35:08,710 --> 00:35:10,420
If it's the second possibility,

670
00:35:10,420 --> 00:35:11,300
and they're smelting

671
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:12,500
and refining inside,

672
00:35:12,900 --> 00:35:13,440
they'd need

673
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:15,030
a lot of equipment and materials.

674
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:16,830
That would also require trucks.

675
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:21,660
Take a look at this book.

676
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:22,470
[Chemistry Handling Technology]

677
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:23,340
It might help.

678
00:35:24,130 --> 00:35:25,380
Besides gold mining,

679
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:26,690
I also pulled the files

680
00:35:26,690 --> 00:35:27,540
on poaching.

681
00:35:28,900 --> 00:35:30,270
Since they were hiding

682
00:35:30,300 --> 00:35:31,150
sheepskins in the truck,

683
00:35:31,150 --> 00:35:32,110
it means this group

684
00:35:32,110 --> 00:35:34,040
is definitely linked to poaching.

685
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:36,850
I'm going to go through them all again.

686
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:45,150
You're getting moldy

687
00:35:45,150 --> 00:35:46,570
staying at the station, aren't you?

688
00:35:46,570 --> 00:35:47,540
Come with me starting tomorrow.

689
00:35:47,540 --> 00:35:48,450
Be my driver.

690
00:35:49,690 --> 00:35:50,830
I still need my hand.

691
00:35:53,730 --> 00:35:54,540
Just go.

692
00:35:55,170 --> 00:35:56,500
You must be bored stiff.

693
00:35:58,900 --> 00:35:59,450
Okay.

694
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:03,470
We can't drop the fertilizer lead either.

695
00:36:03,470 --> 00:36:04,030
He,

696
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:06,070
you and Sangba keep investigating it.

697
00:36:06,070 --> 00:36:06,510
Okay.

698
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:07,690
Han,

699
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:08,690
tomorrow

700
00:36:08,690 --> 00:36:10,030
we're going to the freight company.

701
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:10,490
Okay.

702
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:15,400
Hello?

703
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:17,800
He's here.

704
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,500
Captain, it's for you.

705
00:36:21,130 --> 00:36:21,690
Hello?

706
00:36:23,830 --> 00:36:26,630
I have something to do tomorrow,
so I can't make it.

707
00:36:32,890 --> 00:36:33,430
Okay.

708
00:36:34,330 --> 00:36:34,980
Got it.

709
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:41,360
I'm going to the county for a meeting
tomorrow.

710
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:43,050
What a surprise.

711
00:36:43,410 --> 00:36:44,050
How long has it been

712
00:36:44,050 --> 00:36:45,650
since you were called for a meeting?

713
00:36:45,650 --> 00:36:46,380
I thought the county government

714
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:47,000
had forgotten about you,

715
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,200
Deputy County Mayor.

716
00:36:49,660 --> 00:36:51,920
The municipal research group is coming.

717
00:36:58,230 --> 00:37:00,790
The municipal research group
will arrive tomorrow.

718
00:37:00,790 --> 00:37:02,720
It's a high-level visit this time.

719
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:04,520
Executive Vice Mayor,

720
00:37:04,520 --> 00:37:06,380
Zhao Zhijin, is leading the team.

721
00:37:06,570 --> 00:37:08,950
Leaders from Planning, Economy, Finance,

722
00:37:08,950 --> 00:37:10,470
and Tax are all attending.

723
00:37:11,710 --> 00:37:12,440
You're back.

724
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:13,690
Sit.

725
00:37:14,670 --> 00:37:16,150
I called you two to discuss about

726
00:37:16,150 --> 00:37:16,810
how I should

727
00:37:16,820 --> 00:37:19,020
report to the research group tomorrow.

728
00:37:19,160 --> 00:37:20,670
I'm not worried
about the Uninhabited Zone.

729
00:37:20,670 --> 00:37:22,340
Although there are many difficulties,

730
00:37:22,340 --> 00:37:24,500
at least the protection
and development work

731
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:26,030
hasn't stopped advancing.

732
00:37:26,590 --> 00:37:27,860
What worries me most

733
00:37:28,570 --> 00:37:29,170
is still the issue

734
00:37:29,170 --> 00:37:30,770
of the animal husbandry tax.

735
00:37:31,570 --> 00:37:33,070
I just took a call.

736
00:37:34,210 --> 00:37:36,410
It was from Chief Song of the Tax Bureau.

737
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:38,080
What does he want?

738
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:39,620
Did he say not to mention

739
00:37:39,620 --> 00:37:41,140
reducing or exempting
the animal husbandry tax?

740
00:37:41,140 --> 00:37:42,600
He didn't say it directly.

741
00:37:43,710 --> 00:37:44,610
He just said the higher-ups

742
00:37:44,610 --> 00:37:46,170
know about our current difficulties.

743
00:37:46,170 --> 00:37:48,570
He hopes we pay attention
to how we report it.

744
00:37:48,570 --> 00:37:50,260
Report the problems realistically,

745
00:37:50,260 --> 00:37:50,860
instead of

746
00:37:50,890 --> 00:37:52,750
unilaterally pleading poverty.

747
00:37:54,150 --> 00:37:54,990
This guy.

748
00:37:56,260 --> 00:37:57,460
Don't get triggered.

749
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,670
Let's discuss how to report it.

750
00:38:02,390 --> 00:38:03,650
The theme of this research visit

751
00:38:03,650 --> 00:38:05,710
is economic development and reform.

752
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,490
The animal husbandry tax issue

753
00:38:07,490 --> 00:38:08,650
cannot be bypassed.

754
00:38:10,740 --> 00:38:11,570
We've been wrangling with the Tax Bureau

755
00:38:11,570 --> 00:38:12,880
for over six months.

756
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:14,820
This is a good opportunity

757
00:38:15,170 --> 00:38:15,670
to let them

758
00:38:15,670 --> 00:38:16,480
come here and see

759
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,280
our actual situation.

760
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:18,300
I know.

761
00:38:19,940 --> 00:38:20,980
The animal husbandry tax
should be mentioned,

762
00:38:20,980 --> 00:38:22,240
and must be mentioned.

763
00:38:22,690 --> 00:38:23,820
But should we bring it up at the meeting

764
00:38:23,820 --> 00:38:25,130
or report it separately?

765
00:38:25,130 --> 00:38:26,340
What's your opinion?

766
00:38:27,210 --> 00:38:28,130
Secretary Chen.

767
00:38:28,130 --> 00:38:29,330
Let me say something.

768
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:30,440
Go ahead.

769
00:38:31,090 --> 00:38:32,190
The Provincial Organization Department

770
00:38:32,190 --> 00:38:33,320
just spoke with you.

771
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:35,840
We can't discuss

772
00:38:35,940 --> 00:38:37,200
the specific details.

773
00:38:37,680 --> 00:38:38,650
But the implication

774
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:39,800
is very clear.

775
00:38:41,190 --> 00:38:43,940
At this critical juncture
of selection and assessment,

776
00:38:43,940 --> 00:38:45,800
it's better for you to speak less.

777
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,440
There's nothing to hide.

778
00:38:48,530 --> 00:38:50,130
It was just a normal inquiry.

779
00:38:50,950 --> 00:38:52,360
I just told the truth.

780
00:38:53,150 --> 00:38:54,090
It's just that

781
00:38:54,190 --> 00:38:55,720
I turned a proper interview

782
00:38:55,780 --> 00:38:57,050
into

783
00:38:57,230 --> 00:38:58,430
a grievance session.

784
00:39:00,580 --> 00:39:01,380
After the meeting,

785
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:02,830
when I saw the comrade
from the Organization Department off,

786
00:39:02,830 --> 00:39:04,090
he only said one thing.

787
00:39:04,990 --> 00:39:06,590
It is hard for anyone

788
00:39:07,690 --> 00:39:09,220
to stay in a place like this.

789
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:10,540
That shows the organization

790
00:39:10,540 --> 00:39:11,800
values you.

791
00:39:12,820 --> 00:39:14,880
We are counting on you to get promoted

792
00:39:15,460 --> 00:39:17,660
so you can come back and help our county.

793
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,440
Let me bring it up.

794
00:39:22,170 --> 00:39:23,440
I am older than you,

795
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:25,140
and my education isn't great.

796
00:39:25,690 --> 00:39:26,550
I have no hope

797
00:39:27,010 --> 00:39:28,610
of getting promoted anyway.

798
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:29,910
It is better if I do it.

799
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:31,630
You have spent the last two years

800
00:39:31,630 --> 00:39:33,170
running around the mountains.

801
00:39:33,170 --> 00:39:33,850
If you do it,

802
00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:35,460
can you even explain it clearly?

803
00:39:35,460 --> 00:39:36,070
I have spent more time

804
00:39:36,070 --> 00:39:37,480
in the pastoral areas than you.

805
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:38,170
During the snowstorm,

806
00:39:38,170 --> 00:39:39,510
I visited every township.

807
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:40,610
Do you think I don't know what's going on?

808
00:39:40,610 --> 00:39:41,550
So what if you were there?

809
00:39:41,550 --> 00:39:42,000
Even so,

810
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,240
you don't know as much as I do.

811
00:39:43,240 --> 00:39:44,550
Stop fighting.

812
00:39:45,180 --> 00:39:47,780
I am the Party Secretary.
I will do the talking.

813
00:39:51,710 --> 00:39:53,250
You two are the key leaders.

814
00:39:54,260 --> 00:39:55,170
If you speak up,

815
00:39:55,860 --> 00:39:57,540
there won't be any room left
for negotiation

816
00:39:57,540 --> 00:39:59,660
between the county leadership team
and the higher-ups.

817
00:39:59,660 --> 00:40:00,560
Let me do it.

818
00:40:02,980 --> 00:40:03,860
Everyone

819
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:05,520
has difficulties.

820
00:40:05,860 --> 00:40:06,630
The provincial

821
00:40:06,630 --> 00:40:07,560
and city budgets

822
00:40:07,630 --> 00:40:08,920
are both very tight.

823
00:40:09,630 --> 00:40:09,970
However,

824
00:40:09,970 --> 00:40:12,200
regarding the misappropriation of funds,

825
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:12,860
your county

826
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:13,230
[Zhao Zhicjin]

827
00:40:13,230 --> 00:40:14,090
has two cases.

828
00:40:15,990 --> 00:40:17,790
According to the Health Bureau,

829
00:40:17,820 --> 00:40:20,210
the 50,000 yuan allocated
to the County Hospital

830
00:40:20,210 --> 00:40:21,670
for bathroom renovations

831
00:40:21,780 --> 00:40:23,040
was misappropriated.

832
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:24,920
Also,

833
00:40:25,330 --> 00:40:26,670
our investigation shows that

834
00:40:26,670 --> 00:40:27,940
the 100,000 yuan allocated

835
00:40:27,940 --> 00:40:28,860
by the Provincial Department of Forestry

836
00:40:28,860 --> 00:40:30,110
to the Conservation Station

837
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:31,230
for improving living conditions

838
00:40:31,230 --> 00:40:32,760
was also misappropriated?

839
00:40:36,270 --> 00:40:38,660
What was so urgent
that you had to do this?

840
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:41,600
Can anyone explain these two cases

841
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:43,600
of misappropriation to me?

842
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:45,580
Vice Mayor Zhao,

843
00:40:45,860 --> 00:40:47,470
regarding the use of these funds...

844
00:40:47,470 --> 00:40:48,400
Secretary Chen,

845
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,810
let me explain this.

846
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:51,890
Vice Mayor Zhao,

847
00:40:52,620 --> 00:40:53,820
our county is currently implementing

848
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:54,440
a hygiene care program

849
00:40:54,440 --> 00:40:56,040
for women in pastoral areas.

850
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:58,340
The 50,000 yuan from the County Hospital

851
00:40:58,340 --> 00:40:59,340
was used entirely to purchase

852
00:40:59,340 --> 00:41:01,040
toilet paper and sanitary belts.

853
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:02,810
They were distributed for free

854
00:41:02,910 --> 00:41:04,510
across twenty pastoral villages
in the county.

855
00:41:04,510 --> 00:41:05,400
We also conducted

856
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:07,130
menstrual hygiene education.

857
00:41:07,820 --> 00:41:08,590
As for the 100,000 yuan

858
00:41:08,590 --> 00:41:10,190
from the Department of Forestry,

859
00:41:10,190 --> 00:41:10,700
it was because

860
00:41:10,700 --> 00:41:12,160
just as the funds arrived,

861
00:41:12,710 --> 00:41:13,860
the Manri River within our borders

862
00:41:13,860 --> 00:41:14,920
suddenly dried up.

863
00:41:15,460 --> 00:41:17,170
It severely affected the water supply

864
00:41:17,170 --> 00:41:18,210
for daily life and livestock

865
00:41:18,210 --> 00:41:21,470
for over a thousand herdsmen households
in two townships.

866
00:41:22,390 --> 00:41:23,410
When County Mayor Lin spoke to me

867
00:41:23,410 --> 00:41:24,470
about this matter,

868
00:41:25,340 --> 00:41:26,870
I was also very conflicted.

869
00:41:27,190 --> 00:41:28,850
But the situation was urgent.

870
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:29,460
We didn't have time

871
00:41:29,460 --> 00:41:31,520
to apply for more funding from above.

872
00:41:32,070 --> 00:41:34,070
The county had to handle it this way.

873
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:38,420
If you have a chance

874
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:40,100
to visit those two townships,

875
00:41:40,590 --> 00:41:41,530
you should still see

876
00:41:41,530 --> 00:41:43,110
the crews drilling wells.

877
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:46,030
The herdsmen are very grateful

878
00:41:46,030 --> 00:41:47,630
to the government this time.

879
00:41:48,060 --> 00:41:49,990
The aid money arrived just in time.

880
00:41:50,930 --> 00:41:51,710
This matter

881
00:41:52,130 --> 00:41:52,760
has had a positive effect

882
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,070
on the image of our Party

883
00:41:54,070 --> 00:41:55,300
and the government.

884
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:01,130
Since you brought up the issue

885
00:42:01,130 --> 00:42:02,660
of misappropriated funds,

886
00:42:03,570 --> 00:42:05,500
let's lay everything on the table.

887
00:42:07,950 --> 00:42:08,920
Let's talk about things

888
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:10,520
we haven't reported before.

889
00:42:13,780 --> 00:42:15,180
The county once diverted

890
00:42:15,330 --> 00:42:16,890
road repair funds

891
00:42:17,770 --> 00:42:20,500
to the Mountain Patrol
for mineral exploration.

892
00:42:20,590 --> 00:42:22,520
We even used Mountain Patrol wages

893
00:42:22,570 --> 00:42:24,630
to help herdsmen build heated sheds.

894
00:42:25,620 --> 00:42:26,560
Never mind

895
00:42:26,730 --> 00:42:27,530
the funding.

896
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:29,400
Even when it comes to

897
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:30,630
cow dung for heating,

898
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,420
our cadres often share theirs

899
00:42:32,420 --> 00:42:33,820
with the hospital

900
00:42:34,190 --> 00:42:35,050
and the school.

901
00:42:37,250 --> 00:42:38,250
For years,

902
00:42:39,050 --> 00:42:40,420
we've been surviving like this.

903
00:42:40,420 --> 00:42:41,880
Robbing Peter to pay Paul,

904
00:42:42,020 --> 00:42:43,750
and scraping things together.

905
00:42:46,080 --> 00:42:48,680
You criticized
the County Finance Department

906
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:49,940
for having irregular

907
00:42:49,940 --> 00:42:51,070
funding practices.

908
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:52,400
I accept that.

909
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:55,730
But the root of the problem

910
00:42:55,730 --> 00:42:56,210
isn't that

911
00:42:56,210 --> 00:42:57,730
our cadres acted on a whim

912
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,170
or had selfish motives.

913
00:42:59,810 --> 00:43:01,140
It was out of necessity.

914
00:43:02,820 --> 00:43:03,230
I believe

915
00:43:03,230 --> 00:43:04,620
our comrades in the county

916
00:43:04,620 --> 00:43:06,420
are dedicated to the public good

917
00:43:06,650 --> 00:43:08,000
and can withstand any investigation.
